1
00:01:52,154 --> 00:01:54,906
Chapter One

2
00:01:55,199 --> 00:01:57,325
Once upon a time...

3
00:01:57,409 --> 00:02:02,872
in Nazi-occupied France

4
00:02:08,212 --> 00:02:12,757
1941

5
00:02:35,906 --> 00:02:43,906
(SPEAKING FRENCH)

6
00:02:45,290 --> 00:02:46,582
Go back inside and shut the door.

7
00:02:48,585 --> 00:02:52,046
Julie, get me some water
for my wash up...

8
00:02:53,131 --> 00:02:54,715
then get inside with your sisters.

9
00:03:20,242 --> 00:03:21,367
(SPEAKING FRENCH)

10
00:03:21,451 --> 00:03:22,577
Ready, Papa.

11
00:03:31,378 --> 00:03:32,503
(SPEAKING FRENCH)

12
00:03:32,629 --> 00:03:33,671
Thank you, my darling...

13
00:03:34,006 --> 00:03:35,631
now you go inside
with your sisters.

14
00:03:40,053 --> 00:03:41,137
Don't run.

15
00:03:53,317 --> 00:03:55,818
(MEN SPEAKING GERMAN)

16
00:04:03,827 --> 00:04:04,869
(SPEAKING FRENCH)

17
00:04:04,995 --> 00:04:06,362
Is this the property
of Perrier LaPadite?

18
00:04:06,496 --> 00:04:07,538
I am Perrier LaPadite.

19
00:04:08,916 --> 00:04:12,001
It is a pleasure to meet
you, Monsieur LaPadite...

20
00:04:12,586 --> 00:04:14,545
I am Colonel Hans Landa of the SS.

21
00:04:15,088 --> 00:04:16,172
What can I do for you?

22
00:04:16,673 --> 00:04:19,508
I was hoping you could invite
me inside your home...

23
00:04:19,843 --> 00:04:22,053
and we may have a discussion.

24
00:04:23,513 --> 00:04:25,014
Certainly. After you.

25
00:04:34,107 --> 00:04:36,859
Colonel Landa, this is my family.

26
00:04:46,954 --> 00:04:48,204
Colonel Hans Landa of the SS...

27
00:04:48,622 --> 00:04:49,705
Mademoiselle...

28
00:04:49,790 --> 00:04:51,040
at your service.

29
00:04:51,959 --> 00:04:54,322
The rumours I have
heard in the village

30
00:04:54,323 --> 00:04:56,212
about your family are all true.

31
00:04:59,424 --> 00:05:02,093
Each one of your daughters is
more lovely than the last.

32
00:05:03,303 --> 00:05:04,387
Thank you.

33
00:05:05,597 --> 00:05:06,639
Please...

34
00:05:07,391 --> 00:05:08,432
have a seat.

35
00:05:14,231 --> 00:05:16,265
Suzanne, would you be so good as
to get the Colonel some wine?

36
00:05:17,567 --> 00:05:18,567
But no.

37
00:05:18,735 --> 00:05:21,070
Merci beaucoup, Monsieur
LaPadite, but no wine.

38
00:05:22,072 --> 00:05:26,909
This being a dairy farm, one would
be safe in assuming you have milk?

39
00:05:26,994 --> 00:05:28,077
Yes.

40
00:05:28,161 --> 00:05:29,578
Then milk is what I prefer.

41
00:05:29,913 --> 00:05:30,997
Very well.

42
00:05:32,124 --> 00:05:33,791
Julie, would you mind
closing the window?

43
00:05:54,187 --> 00:05:55,271
Thank you.

44
00:06:11,371 --> 00:06:15,291
Monsieur, to both your
family and your cows...

45
00:06:16,543 --> 00:06:18,002
I say, "Bravo."

46
00:06:19,129 --> 00:06:20,129
Thank you.

47
00:06:21,465 --> 00:06:24,175
Please join me at your table.

48
00:06:25,052 --> 00:06:26,093
Very well.

49
00:06:31,600 --> 00:06:32,641
Monsieur LaPadite...

50
00:06:33,435 --> 00:06:37,646
what we have to discuss would
be better discussed in private.

51
00:06:38,982 --> 00:06:41,400
You'll notice I left
my men outdoors.

52
00:06:42,527 --> 00:06:44,904
If it wouldn't offend
them, could you

53
00:06:44,905 --> 00:06:47,406
ask your lovely ladies
to step outside?

54
00:06:49,201 --> 00:06:50,242
You are right.

55
00:06:51,244 --> 00:06:53,412
Charlotte, would you
take the girls outside?

56
00:06:54,372 --> 00:06:55,873
The Colonel and I need
to have a few words.

57
00:07:07,928 --> 00:07:09,095
Monsieur LaPadite...

58
00:07:10,764 --> 00:07:15,518
I regret to inform you I've
exhausted the extent of my French.

59
00:07:16,812 --> 00:07:18,840
To continue to speak
it so inadequately

60
00:07:18,841 --> 00:07:20,564
would only serve to embarrass me.

61
00:07:20,816 --> 00:07:24,652
However, I've been led to believe
you speak English quite well.

62
00:07:25,987 --> 00:07:27,029
Yes.

63
00:07:27,114 --> 00:07:31,283
Well, it just so happens, I do as
well. This being your house...

64
00:07:31,576 --> 00:07:33,994
I ask your permission
to switch to English...

65
00:07:34,162 --> 00:07:35,830
for the remainder of
the conversation.

66
00:07:37,124 --> 00:07:38,165
By all means.

67
00:07:38,500 --> 00:07:41,669
While I'm very familiar
with you and your family,

68
00:07:41,753 --> 00:07:45,422
I have no way of knowing if you
are familiar with who I am.

69
00:07:46,341 --> 00:07:48,551
Are you aware of my existence?

70
00:07:49,594 --> 00:07:51,762
- Yes.
- This is good.

71
00:07:52,347 --> 00:07:54,257
Now, are you aware of the job I've

72
00:07:54,258 --> 00:07:56,392
been ordered to carry
out in France?

73
00:07:58,728 --> 00:07:59,812
Yes.

74
00:08:00,480 --> 00:08:02,481
Please tell me what you've heard.

75
00:08:03,400 --> 00:08:04,733
I've heard

76
00:08:05,318 --> 00:08:07,438
that the Führer has
put you in charge

77
00:08:07,439 --> 00:08:09,613
of rounding up the
Jews left in France

78
00:08:09,698 --> 00:08:12,616
who are either hiding
or passing for Gentile.

79
00:08:14,035 --> 00:08:16,954
The Führer couldn't have
said it better himself.

80
00:08:18,874 --> 00:08:22,543
But the meaning of your visit,

81
00:08:23,003 --> 00:08:27,214
pleasant though it is,
is mysterious to me.

82
00:08:28,842 --> 00:08:30,586
The Germans looked
through my house

83
00:08:30,587 --> 00:08:32,136
nine months ago for hiding Jews

84
00:08:32,220 --> 00:08:33,846
and found nothing.

85
00:08:35,640 --> 00:08:37,308
I'm aware of that.

86
00:08:37,767 --> 00:08:40,269
I've read the reports
of this area.

87
00:08:42,314 --> 00:08:45,524
But like any enterprise,
when under new management,

88
00:08:45,609 --> 00:08:48,694
there is always a slight
duplication of efforts,

89
00:08:49,905 --> 00:08:52,120
most of it being a
complete waste of

90
00:08:52,121 --> 00:08:54,575
time, but needs to be
done nevertheless.

91
00:08:55,577 --> 00:08:58,662
I just have a few questions,
Monsieur LaPadite.

92
00:09:00,123 --> 00:09:02,416
If you can assist me with answers,

93
00:09:02,500 --> 00:09:05,586
my department can close
the file on your family.

94
00:09:14,054 --> 00:09:15,221
Now,

95
00:09:16,890 --> 00:09:21,185
before the occupation, there were
four Jewish families in this area,

96
00:09:21,728 --> 00:09:24,063
all dairy farmers like yourself.

97
00:09:25,899 --> 00:09:30,527
Doleracs, Rollins, the Loveitts

98
00:09:32,322 --> 00:09:33,989
and the Dreyfuses.

99
00:09:34,157 --> 00:09:35,741
Is that correct?

100
00:09:35,825 --> 00:09:36,909
To my knowledge,

101
00:09:36,993 --> 00:09:40,454
those were the Jewish families
among the dairy farmers.

102
00:09:40,538 --> 00:09:44,375
Herr Colonel, would it disturb
you if I smoked my pipe?

103
00:09:44,459 --> 00:09:45,918
Please, Monsieur LaPadite,

104
00:09:46,002 --> 00:09:48,963
this is your house, make
yourself comfortable.

105
00:09:49,297 --> 00:09:52,258
Now, according to these papers,

106
00:09:53,176 --> 00:09:56,637
all the Jewish families in this
area have been accounted for

107
00:09:56,721 --> 00:09:59,556
except the Dreyfuses.

108
00:10:00,976 --> 00:10:04,436
Somewhere in the last year it
would appear they've vanished.

109
00:10:04,521 --> 00:10:06,168
Which leads me to
the conclusion that

110
00:10:06,169 --> 00:10:07,815
they've either made
good their escape

111
00:10:07,899 --> 00:10:10,776
or someone is very
successfully hiding them.

112
00:10:11,987 --> 00:10:15,614
What have you heard about the
Dreyfuses, Monsieur LaPadite?

113
00:10:15,699 --> 00:10:18,033
- Only rumours.
- I love rumours.

114
00:10:19,619 --> 00:10:20,995
Facts could be so misleading,

115
00:10:21,079 --> 00:10:24,248
where rumours, true or
false, are often revealing.

116
00:10:24,624 --> 00:10:26,125
So, Monsieur LaPadite,

117
00:10:26,209 --> 00:10:29,461
what rumours have you heard
regarding the Dreyfuses?

118
00:10:32,215 --> 00:10:35,426
Again, this is just a rumour,

119
00:10:35,510 --> 00:10:41,807
but we heard the Dreyfuses had
made their way into Spain.

120
00:10:49,649 --> 00:10:52,526
So, the rumours you've
heard have been of escape?

121
00:10:52,610 --> 00:10:54,028
(AGREES IN FRENCH)

122
00:10:54,112 --> 00:10:55,195
Yes.

123
00:10:58,742 --> 00:11:02,536
Having never met the Dreyfuses,
would you confirm for me

124
00:11:02,620 --> 00:11:05,873
the exact members of the
household and their names?

125
00:11:11,338 --> 00:11:13,297
There were five of them.

126
00:11:15,508 --> 00:11:18,177
The father, Jacob.

127
00:11:20,013 --> 00:11:22,514
Wife, Miram.

128
00:11:24,559 --> 00:11:28,187
And her brother, Bob.

129
00:11:35,403 --> 00:11:36,945
How old is Bob?

130
00:11:38,573 --> 00:11:39,907
Thirty, 31.

131
00:11:44,204 --> 00:11:45,412
Continue.

132
00:11:45,789 --> 00:11:47,414
And the children,

133
00:11:49,167 --> 00:11:50,250
Amos

134
00:11:52,379 --> 00:11:53,837
and Shosanna.

135
00:11:56,007 --> 00:11:57,800
Ages of the children?

136
00:12:04,891 --> 00:12:08,477
Amos was nine or 10.

137
00:12:11,356 --> 00:12:14,817
- And Shosanna?
- And Shosanna was

138
00:12:16,486 --> 00:12:20,322
18 or 19. I'm not really sure.

139
00:12:31,167 --> 00:12:33,502
Well, I guess that should do it.

140
00:12:39,968 --> 00:12:42,007
However, before I go, could I have

141
00:12:42,008 --> 00:12:44,346
another glass of
your delicious milk?

142
00:12:47,350 --> 00:12:48,851
But of course.

143
00:12:55,692 --> 00:12:57,651
Monsieur LaPadite,

144
00:12:57,735 --> 00:13:01,738
are you aware of the nickname the
people of France have given me?

145
00:13:05,368 --> 00:13:07,870
I have no interest in such things.

146
00:13:08,872 --> 00:13:11,540
But you are aware of
what they call me.

147
00:13:14,169 --> 00:13:15,502
I'm aware.

148
00:13:17,213 --> 00:13:19,047
What are you aware of?

149
00:13:26,389 --> 00:13:28,098
(THANKING IN FRENCH)

150
00:13:29,017 --> 00:13:31,394
That they call you
"The Jew Hunter."

151
00:13:31,395 --> 00:13:32,395
Precisely.

152
00:13:34,439 --> 00:13:37,107
I understand your trepidation
in repeating it.

153
00:13:37,233 --> 00:13:39,485
Heydrich apparently
hates the moniker

154
00:13:39,569 --> 00:13:42,196
the good people of Prague
have bestowed on him.

155
00:13:42,280 --> 00:13:43,999
Actually, why he
would hate the name

156
00:13:44,000 --> 00:13:45,532
"the Hangman" is baffling to me.

157
00:13:45,617 --> 00:13:47,042
It would appear he has done

158
00:13:47,043 --> 00:13:48,994
everything in his
power to earn it.

159
00:13:49,078 --> 00:13:52,331
Now I, on the other hand,
love my unofficial title

160
00:13:52,415 --> 00:13:54,791
precisely because I've earned it.

161
00:13:56,252 --> 00:14:00,297
The feature that makes me such an
effective hunter of the Jews is,

162
00:14:00,423 --> 00:14:03,050
as opposed to most
German soldiers,

163
00:14:03,134 --> 00:14:05,135
I can think like a Jew

164
00:14:05,803 --> 00:14:08,555
where they can only
think like a German.

165
00:14:08,932 --> 00:14:11,642
More precisely, a German soldier.

166
00:14:18,066 --> 00:14:20,711
Now, if one were to
determine what attribute

167
00:14:20,712 --> 00:14:22,945
the German people
share with a beast,

168
00:14:23,488 --> 00:14:27,074
it would be the cunning and the
predatory instinct of a hawk.

169
00:14:27,492 --> 00:14:29,221
But if one were to determine what

170
00:14:29,222 --> 00:14:31,370
attributes the Jews
share with a beast,

171
00:14:31,454 --> 00:14:33,580
it would be that of the rat.

172
00:14:36,334 --> 00:14:38,221
The Führer and
Goebbels' propaganda

173
00:14:38,222 --> 00:14:40,212
have said pretty
much the same thing.

174
00:14:40,296 --> 00:14:43,298
But where our conclusions differ,

175
00:14:43,424 --> 00:14:46,426
is I don't consider the
comparison an insult.

176
00:14:48,930 --> 00:14:52,766
Consider for a moment the
world a rat lives in.

177
00:14:53,643 --> 00:14:55,811
It's a hostile world, indeed.

178
00:14:56,646 --> 00:15:00,065
If a rat were to scamper through
your front door, right now,

179
00:15:00,149 --> 00:15:02,609
would you greet it with hostility?

180
00:15:03,528 --> 00:15:05,404
I suppose I would.

181
00:15:05,488 --> 00:15:07,800
Has a rat ever done
anything to you to

182
00:15:07,801 --> 00:15:10,409
create this animosity
you feel toward them?

183
00:15:11,327 --> 00:15:13,912
Rats spread disease.
They bite people.

184
00:15:14,497 --> 00:15:18,250
Rats were the cause of the bubonic
plague, but that's some time ago.

185
00:15:18,334 --> 00:15:20,961
I propose to you any disease
a rat could spread,

186
00:15:21,045 --> 00:15:23,505
a squirrel could equally carry.

187
00:15:23,590 --> 00:15:25,215
Would you agree?

188
00:15:25,341 --> 00:15:26,967
(AGREES IN FRENCH)

189
00:15:27,051 --> 00:15:29,636
Yet, I assume you don't share the
same animosity with squirrels

190
00:15:29,721 --> 00:15:32,514
- that you do with rats, do you?
- No.

191
00:15:32,932 --> 00:15:35,434
Yet, they're both
rodents, are they not?

192
00:15:35,518 --> 00:15:39,521
And except for the tail, they even
rather look alike, don't they?

193
00:15:39,897 --> 00:15:42,733
It's an interesting
thought, Herr Colonel.

194
00:15:43,443 --> 00:15:45,485
However interesting as
the thought may be,

195
00:15:45,570 --> 00:15:48,864
it makes not one bit of
difference to how you feel.

196
00:15:51,200 --> 00:15:55,245
If a rat were to walk in here,
right now, as I'm talking

197
00:15:56,372 --> 00:16:00,250
would you greet it with a
saucer of your delicious milk?

198
00:16:00,376 --> 00:16:01,793
Probably not.

199
00:16:02,462 --> 00:16:04,129
I didn't think so.

200
00:16:04,756 --> 00:16:06,298
You don't like them.

201
00:16:06,382 --> 00:16:08,300
You don't really know why
you don't like them.

202
00:16:08,384 --> 00:16:11,094
All you know is you
find them repulsive.

203
00:16:13,306 --> 00:16:16,391
Consequently, a German
soldier conducts a search

204
00:16:16,476 --> 00:16:18,977
of a house suspected
of hiding Jews.

205
00:16:19,896 --> 00:16:21,480
Where does the hawk look?

206
00:16:21,564 --> 00:16:24,775
He looks in the barn, he looks in
the attic, he looks in the cellar,

207
00:16:24,901 --> 00:16:27,277
he looks everywhere he would hide.

208
00:16:28,237 --> 00:16:30,534
But there are so
many places it would

209
00:16:30,535 --> 00:16:32,407
never occur to a hawk to hide.

210
00:16:34,661 --> 00:16:38,330
However, the reason the Führer has
brought me off my Alps in Austria

211
00:16:38,414 --> 00:16:40,564
and placed me in
French cow country

212
00:16:40,565 --> 00:16:42,834
today is because it
does occur to me.

213
00:16:44,087 --> 00:16:47,464
Because I'm aware what tremendous
feats human beings are capable of

214
00:16:47,590 --> 00:16:49,591
once they abandon dignity.

215
00:16:51,344 --> 00:16:53,470
May I smoke my pipe as well?

216
00:16:55,807 --> 00:16:58,684
Please, Herr Colonel,
make yourself at home.

217
00:17:11,447 --> 00:17:16,535
Now, my job dictates

218
00:17:21,874 --> 00:17:24,543
that I must have my
men enter your home

219
00:17:28,464 --> 00:17:30,382
and conduct a thorough search

220
00:17:30,466 --> 00:17:34,219
before I can officially cross
your family's name off my list.

221
00:17:34,971 --> 00:17:36,982
And if there are any
irregularities to

222
00:17:36,983 --> 00:17:38,890
be found, rest assured
they will be.

223
00:17:38,975 --> 00:17:41,184
That is unless you have
something to tell me

224
00:17:41,310 --> 00:17:44,271
that makes the conducting
of a search unnecessary.

225
00:17:44,355 --> 00:17:46,606
I might add, also,
that any information

226
00:17:46,691 --> 00:17:48,966
that makes the
performance of my duty

227
00:17:48,967 --> 00:17:51,361
easier will not be
met with punishment.

228
00:17:52,196 --> 00:17:55,741
Actually, quite the contrary.
It will be met with reward.

229
00:17:56,242 --> 00:17:57,576
And that reward will be,

230
00:17:57,660 --> 00:18:00,412
your family will cease to
be harassed in any way

231
00:18:00,496 --> 00:18:02,825
by the German military
during the rest

232
00:18:02,826 --> 00:18:04,916
of our occupation of your country.

233
00:18:15,595 --> 00:18:18,930
You're sheltering enemies
of the state, are you not?

234
00:18:24,270 --> 00:18:25,353
Yes.

235
00:18:28,274 --> 00:18:32,194
You're sheltering them underneath
your floorboards, aren't you?

236
00:18:34,739 --> 00:18:35,822
Yes.

237
00:18:38,618 --> 00:18:41,661
Point out to me the areas
where they're hiding.

238
00:19:02,683 --> 00:19:04,059
Since I haven't heard
any disturbance,

239
00:19:04,143 --> 00:19:07,854
I assume, while they're listening,
they don't speak English.

240
00:19:09,774 --> 00:19:10,857
Yes.

241
00:19:12,902 --> 00:19:14,320
I'm going to switch
back to French now,

242
00:19:14,321 --> 00:19:15,737
and I want you to
follow my masquerade.

243
00:19:15,822 --> 00:19:17,322
Is that clear?

244
00:19:19,242 --> 00:19:20,325
Yes.

245
00:19:21,494 --> 00:19:22,536
(SPEAKING FRENCH)

246
00:19:22,620 --> 00:19:23,703
Monsieur LaPadite...

247
00:19:25,665 --> 00:19:28,416
I thank you for the milk...

248
00:19:30,336 --> 00:19:31,419
and your hospitality.

249
00:19:34,173 --> 00:19:36,132
I do believe our
business here is done.

250
00:19:41,180 --> 00:19:42,389
Ah, ladies.

251
00:19:45,560 --> 00:19:48,645
I thank you for your time.

252
00:19:51,190 --> 00:19:52,858
We shan't be bothering
your family any longer.

253
00:19:53,901 --> 00:19:54,943
So, Monsieur...

254
00:19:55,987 --> 00:19:57,028
Mademoiselle.

255
00:19:57,530 --> 00:20:00,365
I bid farewell to you and say...

256
00:20:00,908 --> 00:20:01,992
adieu.

257
00:20:22,263 --> 00:20:23,346
It's the girl.

258
00:21:09,644 --> 00:21:12,187
Goodbye, Shosanna.

259
00:21:21,489 --> 00:21:23,949
Chapter Two

260
