1159
01:16:09,815 --> 01:16:10,941
Before we go on playing...

1160
01:16:11,484 --> 01:16:12,567
we will drink.

1161
01:16:13,611 --> 01:16:15,737
We drink to our friend Wilhelm.

1162
01:16:17,490 --> 01:16:18,657
And his little boy...

1163
01:16:19,659 --> 01:16:20,659
Maximilian.

1164
01:16:21,077 --> 01:16:22,160
(ALL TOASTING IN GERMAN)

1165
01:16:22,245 --> 01:16:23,411
- To Max.
- To Max.

1166
01:16:23,496 --> 01:16:24,579
(SPEAKING GERMAN)

1167
01:16:24,664 --> 01:16:25,914
There's some new development.

1168
01:16:25,998 --> 01:16:27,499
The cinema venue has changed.

1169
01:16:27,959 --> 01:16:29,000
Why?

1170
01:16:29,126 --> 01:16:31,086
No one knows but that should
not be a real problem.

1171
01:16:31,754 --> 01:16:33,152
The cinema it's been changed to is

1172
01:16:33,153 --> 01:16:34,673
considerably smaller
than The Ritz.

1173
01:16:35,424 --> 01:16:37,328
So whatever explosives
you brought for The

1174
01:16:37,329 --> 01:16:39,010
Ritz should be doubly
effective here.

1175
01:16:42,682 --> 01:16:44,015
Now the next piece
of information...

1176
01:16:44,517 --> 01:16:45,600
is colossal.

1177
01:16:45,810 --> 01:16:47,185
Try not to overreact.

1178
01:16:49,522 --> 01:16:50,605
The Führer...

1179
01:16:52,525 --> 01:16:53,692
(SPEAKING GERMAN)

1180
01:16:53,776 --> 01:16:54,859
I was just thinking...

1181
01:16:55,361 --> 01:16:58,196
could you sign an autograph
to my son on his birthday?

1182
01:17:00,157 --> 01:17:02,367
Of course. I'd love to, Wilhelm.

1183
01:17:03,369 --> 01:17:06,871
This handsome Staff Sergeant
just became a father today.

1184
01:17:07,290 --> 01:17:08,331
Congratulations.

1185
01:17:09,875 --> 01:17:10,959
Thank you.

1186
01:17:11,043 --> 01:17:12,711
Do you know the name
of this progeny yet?

1187
01:17:13,546 --> 01:17:18,550
I most certainly do, Fräulein.
His name is Maximilian.

1188
01:17:19,010 --> 01:17:20,552
Maximilian, wonderful name.

1189
01:17:22,722 --> 01:17:24,306
Thank you, Lieutenant.

1190
01:17:26,726 --> 01:17:29,561
Nothing but the best
for little Maximilian.

1191
01:17:29,729 --> 01:17:31,521
(THANKING IN GERMAN)

1192
01:17:36,235 --> 01:17:39,696
Max may not know who
you are now but...

1193
01:17:40,906 --> 01:17:43,074
he will. I will show him
all of your movies.

1194
01:17:43,576 --> 01:17:44,576
Good.

1195
01:17:44,702 --> 01:17:46,745
He will grow up with
your films and...

1196
01:17:49,415 --> 01:17:51,249
this napkin on his wall.

1197
01:17:51,751 --> 01:17:57,255
I propose a toast to the
greatest actress in Germany.

1198
01:17:57,506 --> 01:18:01,926
There is no Dietrich. There is no
Riefenstahl. Only Von Hammersmark.

1199
01:18:03,387 --> 01:18:04,554
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

1200
01:18:05,264 --> 01:18:06,306
Cheers.

1201
01:18:11,562 --> 01:18:12,771
Once again...

1202
01:18:15,483 --> 01:18:16,566
(SPEAKING GERMAN)

1203
01:18:16,650 --> 01:18:19,319
Frau Hammersmark, what
brings you to France?

1204
01:18:20,863 --> 01:18:22,614
None of your business.

1205
01:18:23,699 --> 01:18:24,741
Staff Sergeant.

1206
01:18:27,119 --> 01:18:30,372
You might not have worn
out your welcome with

1207
01:18:30,456 --> 01:18:33,333
the Fräulein with your
drunken boorish behaviour...

1208
01:18:34,085 --> 01:18:35,585
but you have worn out
your welcome with me.

1209
01:18:37,463 --> 01:18:39,678
Might I remind you,
Staff Sergeant,

1210
01:18:39,679 --> 01:18:41,216
you are an enlisted man.

1211
01:18:41,425 --> 01:18:43,134
This is an officer's table.

1212
01:18:45,638 --> 01:18:49,057
I suggest you stop
pestering the Fräulein...

1213
01:18:49,809 --> 01:18:51,643
and rejoin your table.

1214
01:18:57,400 --> 01:19:02,278
Excuse me, Captain, but your
accent is very unusual.

1215
01:19:05,449 --> 01:19:06,491
Where are you from?

1216
01:19:09,537 --> 01:19:12,747
You must be either completely
drunk or mad to dare...

1217
01:19:13,124 --> 01:19:15,291
to speak to a superior officer
with such impertinentness.

1218
01:19:15,835 --> 01:19:17,001
Staff Sergeant.

1219
01:19:18,462 --> 01:19:20,130
I'm making you and you
responsible for him.

1220
01:19:20,256 --> 01:19:21,623
I suggest you take
hold of your friend...

1221
01:19:21,632 --> 01:19:23,619
or he'll spend Max's
first birthday

1222
01:19:23,620 --> 01:19:25,385
in jail for public drunkenness.

1223
01:19:25,469 --> 01:19:26,636
(SPEAKING GERMAN)

1224
01:19:26,720 --> 01:19:27,804
Might I inquire?

1225
01:19:59,503 --> 01:20:01,337
Like our young newly
christened father here...

1226
01:20:02,506 --> 01:20:04,924
I, too, have an acute
ear for accents.

1227
01:20:08,554 --> 01:20:09,596
And like him...

1228
01:20:10,723 --> 01:20:12,140
I, too, find yours odd.

1229
01:20:14,518 --> 01:20:15,685
From where do you hail, Captain?

1230
01:20:16,187 --> 01:20:17,270
Major, this is highly...

1231
01:20:17,354 --> 01:20:19,606
I wasn't speaking to
you, Lieutenant Munich.

1232
01:20:20,983 --> 01:20:23,568
Or you either,
Lieutenant Frankfurt.

1233
01:20:25,488 --> 01:20:30,200
I was speaking to Captain
I-don't-know-what.

1234
01:20:34,580 --> 01:20:39,083
I was born in a village that rests
in the shadow of the Piz Palü.

1235
01:20:39,919 --> 01:20:41,252
- The mountain?
- Yes.

1236
01:20:42,254 --> 01:20:43,755
In that village, we
all speak like this.

1237
01:20:45,424 --> 01:20:47,634
Have you seen the
Riefenstahl film?

1238
01:20:48,761 --> 01:20:50,595
- Yes.
- Then you saw me.

1239
01:20:52,223 --> 01:20:55,266
You remember the
skiing torch scene?

1240
01:20:57,102 --> 01:20:58,144
Yes.

1241
01:20:59,146 --> 01:21:02,209
In that scene was
myself, my father,

1242
01:21:02,210 --> 01:21:04,776
my sister and my two brothers.

1243
01:21:06,320 --> 01:21:08,112
My brother is so handsome...

1244
01:21:08,572 --> 01:21:12,116
the director Pabst,
gave him a Close-Up.

1245
01:21:12,993 --> 01:21:16,412
Herr Major, if my word
means anything...

1246
01:21:17,122 --> 01:21:20,959
I can vouch for everything the
young Captain has just said.

1247
01:21:22,461 --> 01:21:24,963
He does hail from the
bottom of the Piz Palü.

1248
01:21:25,589 --> 01:21:30,176
He was in the film and his brother
is far more handsome than he.

1249
01:21:40,646 --> 01:21:42,188
You should rejoin your friends.

1250
01:21:46,402 --> 01:21:47,443
May I join you?

1251
01:21:47,528 --> 01:21:48,611
By all means.

1252
01:21:49,738 --> 01:21:50,780
Wunderbar.

1253
01:21:58,080 --> 01:22:01,666
So that's the source of
your bizarre accent.

1254
01:22:03,168 --> 01:22:04,210
That's extraordinary.

1255
01:22:04,920 --> 01:22:05,962
What are you doing here?

1256
01:22:06,338 --> 01:22:09,340
Aside from having a drink
with the lovely Fräulein?

1257
01:22:10,342 --> 01:22:12,969
Well, that pleasure
requires no explanation.

1258
01:22:14,179 --> 01:22:15,388
I mean in country.

1259
01:22:17,016 --> 01:22:19,809
You're obviously not stationed in
France or I'd know who you are.

1260
01:22:20,561 --> 01:22:22,353
You know every German in France?

1261
01:22:23,188 --> 01:22:24,272
Worth knowing.

1262
01:22:30,529 --> 01:22:32,280
Well, there lies the problem.

1263
01:22:33,073 --> 01:22:34,574
We never claimed to
be worth knowing.

1264
01:22:35,826 --> 01:22:37,493
All levity aside, what
are you doing in France?

1265
01:22:39,204 --> 01:22:42,165
Attending Minister Goebbels' film
premiere as the Fräulein's escort.

